{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"\"Jó napot, pacák\" Which,\nas somebody here must surely know,"},{"time":6000,"text":"means \"What's up, guys?\" in Magyar,"},{"time":9000,"text":"that peculiar non-Indo-European\nlanguage spoken by Hungarians"},{"time":12000,"text":"for which, given the fact\nthat cognitive diversity is"},{"time":15000,"text":"at least as threatened\nas biodiversity on this planet,"},{"time":18000,"text":"few would have imagined much\nof a future even a century or two ago."},{"time":22000,"text":"But there it is: \"Jó napot, pacák\""},{"time":24000,"text":"I said somebody here must\nsurely know, because"},{"time":28000,"text":"despite the fact that there aren't\nthat many Hungarians to begin with,"},{"time":31334,"text":"and the further fact that, so far\nas I know, there's not a drop"},{"time":34334,"text":"of Hungarian blood in my veins,\nat every critical juncture of my life"},{"time":38000,"text":"there has been a Hungarian friend\nor mentor there beside me."},{"time":42000,"text":"I even have dreams that take\nplace in landscapes"},{"time":44310,"text":"I recognize as the landscapes\nof Hungarian films,"},{"time":48000,"text":"especially the early\nmovies of Miklos Jancso."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"So, how do I explain this\nmysterious affinity?"},{"time":55000,"text":"Maybe it's because my native\nstate of South Carolina,"},{"time":60000,"text":"which is not much smaller\nthan present-day Hungary,"},{"time":63000,"text":"once imagined a future for itself\nas an independent country."},{"time":66000,"text":"And as a consequence of that presumption,"},{"time":68000,"text":"my hometown was burned\nto the ground by an invading army,"},{"time":72000,"text":"an experience that has befallen\nmany a Hungarian town and village"},{"time":76000,"text":"throughout its long and troubled history."},{"time":79000,"text":"Or maybe it's because when\nI was a teenager back in the '50s,"},{"time":82000,"text":"my uncle Henry -- having\ndenounced the Ku Klux Klan"},{"time":85000,"text":"and been bombed for his trouble\nand had crosses burned in his yard,"},{"time":89000,"text":"living under death threat -- took his wife\nand children to Massachusetts for safety"},{"time":93000,"text":"and went back to South Carolina\nto face down the Klan alone."},{"time":96000,"text":"That was a very Hungarian thing to do,"},{"time":99000,"text":"as anyone will attest who remembers 1956."},{"time":103000,"text":"And of course, from time\nto time Hungarians"},{"time":106000,"text":"have invented\ntheir own equivalent of the Klan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108263,"text":"Well, it seems to me that this\nHungarian presence in my life"},{"time":115000,"text":"is difficult to account for, but ultimately\nI ascribe it to an admiration"},{"time":121000,"text":"for people with a complex moral awareness,"},{"time":124000,"text":"with a heritage of guilt and defeat\nmatched by defiance and bravado."},{"time":129000,"text":"It's not a typical mindset\nfor most Americans,"},{"time":132000,"text":"but it is perforce typical\nof virtually all Hungarians."},{"time":136000,"text":"So, \"Jó napot, pacák!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"I went back to South Carolina\nafter some 15 years amid the alien corn"},{"time":143000,"text":"at the tail end of the 1960s,"},{"time":146000,"text":"with the reckless\ncondescension of that era"},{"time":149000,"text":"thinking I would save my people."},{"time":151000,"text":"Never mind the fact that they were slow\nto acknowledge they needed saving."},{"time":155000,"text":"I labored in that vineyard\nfor a quarter century before"},{"time":158000,"text":"making my way to a little kingdom\nof the just in upstate South Carolina,"},{"time":162000,"text":"a Methodist-affiliated institution\nof higher learning called Wofford College."},{"time":166000,"text":"I knew nothing about Wofford"},{"time":168000,"text":"and even less about Methodism,"},{"time":170000,"text":"but I was reassured on the first day\nthat I taught at Wofford College"},{"time":174000,"text":"to find, among the auditors\nin my classroom,"},{"time":176120,"text":"a 90-year-old Hungarian, surrounded\nby a bevy of middle-aged European women"},{"time":183000,"text":"who seemed to function\nas an entourage of Rhinemaidens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185644,"text":"His name was Sandor Teszler."},{"time":188000,"text":"He was a puckish widower\nwhose wife and children were dead"},{"time":192000,"text":"and whose grandchildren lived far away."},{"time":195000,"text":"In appearance, he resembled\nMahatma Gandhi,"},{"time":198000,"text":"minus the loincloth,\nplus orthopedic boots."},{"time":201000,"text":"He had been born in 1903 in the provinces"},{"time":205000,"text":"of the old Austro-Hungarian Empire,"},{"time":207000,"text":"in what later would become Yugoslavia."},{"time":210000,"text":"He was ostracized as a child,\nnot because he was a Jew --"},{"time":213000,"text":"his parents weren't very\nreligious anyhow --"},{"time":214000,"text":"but because he had been born\nwith two club feet,"},{"time":217000,"text":"a condition which, in those days,\nrequired institutionalization"},{"time":222000,"text":"and a succession of painful operations\nbetween the ages of one and 11."},{"time":226000,"text":"He went to the commercial business\nhigh school as a young man"},{"time":229000,"text":"in Budapest, and there\nhe was as smart as he was modest"},{"time":234000,"text":"and he enjoyed a considerable success.\nAnd after graduation"},{"time":237000,"text":"when he went into textile\nengineering, the success continued."},{"time":240000,"text":"He built one plant after another."},{"time":242000,"text":"He married and had two sons. He\nhad friends in high places who"},{"time":245000,"text":"assured him that he was of great\nvalue to the economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"Once, as he had left\ninstructions to have done,"},{"time":253000,"text":"he was summoned in the middle of the night\nby the night watchman at one of his plants."},{"time":256000,"text":"The night watchman had caught\nan employee who was stealing socks --"},{"time":261000,"text":"it was a hosiery mill, and he simply\nbacked a truck up to the loading dock"},{"time":264000,"text":"and was shoveling in mountains of socks."},{"time":265000,"text":"Mr. Teszler went down to the plant\nand confronted the thief and said,"},{"time":269000,"text":"\"But why do you steal from me? If you\nneed money you have only to ask.\""},{"time":274000,"text":"The night watchman, seeing how things\nwere going and waxing indignant,"},{"time":278000,"text":"said, \"Well, we're going to call\nthe police, aren't we?\""},{"time":280000,"text":"But Mr. Teszler answered, \"No,\nthat will not be necessary."},{"time":283000,"text":"He will not steal from us again.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"Well, maybe he was too trusting,\nbecause he stayed where he was"},{"time":290000,"text":"long after the Nazi Anschluss in Austria"},{"time":292000,"text":"and even after the arrests\nand deportations began in Budapest."},{"time":297000,"text":"He took the simple precaution of having\ncyanide capsules placed in lockets"},{"time":301000,"text":"that could be worn about the necks\nof himself and his family."},{"time":304000,"text":"And then one day, it happened:\nhe and his family were arrested"},{"time":308000,"text":"and they were taken to a death\nhouse on the Danube."},{"time":311000,"text":"In those early days of the Final\nSolution, it was handcrafted brutality;"},{"time":315000,"text":"people were beaten to death\nand their bodies tossed into the river."},{"time":319000,"text":"But none who entered that death\nhouse had ever come out alive."},{"time":323000,"text":"And in a twist you would not believe\nin a Steven Spielberg film --"},{"time":327000,"text":"the Gauleiter who was overseeing this\nbrutal beating was the very same thief"},{"time":332000,"text":"who had stolen socks\nfrom Mr. Teszler's hosiery mill."},{"time":336000,"text":"It was a brutal beating. And\nmidway through that brutality,"},{"time":341000,"text":"one of Mr. Teszler's sons,\nAndrew, looked up and said,"},{"time":344000,"text":"\"Is it time to take\nthe capsule now, Papa?\""},{"time":347000,"text":"And the Gauleiter, who afterwards\nvanishes from this story,"},{"time":351000,"text":"leaned down and whispered\ninto Mr. Teszler's ear,"},{"time":354000,"text":"\"No, do not take the capsule.\nHelp is on the way.\""},{"time":357000,"text":"And then resumed the beating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359000,"text":"But help was on the way,\nand shortly afterwards"},{"time":361263,"text":"a car arrived from the Swiss Embassy."},{"time":364000,"text":"They were spirited to safety. They\nwere reclassified as Yugoslav citizens"},{"time":368000,"text":"and they managed to stay\none step ahead of their pursuers"},{"time":371000,"text":"for the duration of the War,\nsurviving burnings and bombings"},{"time":375000,"text":"and, at the end of the War,\narrest by the Soviets."},{"time":377405,"text":"Probably, Mr. Teszler had gotten\nsome money into Swiss bank accounts"},{"time":381000,"text":"because he managed to take\nhis family first to Great Britain,"},{"time":385000,"text":"then to Long Island and then to the center\nof the textile industry in the American South."},{"time":389263,"text":"Which, as chance would have it,\nwas Spartanburg, South Carolina,"},{"time":393000,"text":"the location of Wofford College."},{"time":395000,"text":"And there, Mr. Teszler began all over again\nand once again achieved immense success,"},{"time":401000,"text":"especially after he invented the process"},{"time":403000,"text":"for manufacturing a new\nfabric called double-knit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"And then in the late 1950s, in the aftermath\nof Brown v. Board of Education,"},{"time":413000,"text":"when the Klan was resurgent\nall over the South,"},{"time":416000,"text":"Mr. Teszler said, \"I have\nheard this talk before.\""},{"time":420000,"text":"And he called his top\nassistant to him and asked,"},{"time":425000,"text":"\"Where would you say, in this\nregion, racism is most virulent?\""},{"time":428000,"text":"\"Well, I don't rightly know, Mr. Teszler.\nI reckon that would be Kings Mountain.\""},{"time":433000,"text":"\"Good. Buy us some land in Kings Mountain"},{"time":437000,"text":"and announce we are going\nto build a major plant there.\""},{"time":439000,"text":"The man did as he was told,\nand shortly afterwards,"},{"time":442000,"text":"Mr. Teszler received a visit\nfrom the white mayor of Kings Mountain."},{"time":446000,"text":"Now, you should know that at that time,"},{"time":449000,"text":"the textile industry in the South\nwas notoriously segregated."},{"time":452000,"text":"The white mayor visited\nMr. Teszler and said,"},{"time":456000,"text":"\"Mr. Teszler, I trust you’re going\nto be hiring a lot of white workers.\""},{"time":459453,"text":"Mr. Teszler told him, \"You bring me\nthe best workers that you can find,"},{"time":463000,"text":"and if they are good\nenough, I will hire them.\""},{"time":465263,"text":"He also received a visit from the leader\nof the black community,"},{"time":470000,"text":"a minister, who said, \"Mr. Teszler,\nI sure hope you're going to"},{"time":472000,"text":"hire some black workers\nfor this new plant of yours.\""},{"time":474548,"text":"He got the same answer: \"You bring\nthe best workers that you can find,"},{"time":478000,"text":"and if they are good\nenough, I will hire them.\""},{"time":481000,"text":"As it happens, the black minister did\nhis job better than the white mayor,"},{"time":484477,"text":"but that's neither here or there."},{"time":485477,"text":"Mr. Teszler hired 16 men:\neight white, eight black."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"They were to be his seed\ngroup, his future foremen."},{"time":492000,"text":"He had installed the heavy\nequipment for his new process"},{"time":495000,"text":"in an abandoned store\nin the vicinity of Kings Mountain,"},{"time":498000,"text":"and for two months these 16 men\nwould live and work together,"},{"time":501000,"text":"mastering the new process."},{"time":502000,"text":"He gathered them together\nafter an initial tour of that facility"},{"time":506000,"text":"and he asked if there were any questions."},{"time":508000,"text":"There was hemming and hawing\nand shuffling of feet,"},{"time":510453,"text":"and then one of the white workers\nstepped forward and said,"},{"time":515000,"text":"\"Well, yeah. We’ve looked at this place\nand there's only one place to sleep,"},{"time":518000,"text":"there's only one place to eat,\nthere's only one bathroom,"},{"time":521000,"text":"there's only one water fountain. Is this\nplant going to be integrated or what?\""},{"time":527000,"text":"Mr. Teszler said, \"You are being paid twice the wages\nof any other textile workers in this region"},{"time":532000,"text":"and this is how we do business.\nDo you have any other questions?\""},{"time":536000,"text":"\"No, I reckon I don't.\""},{"time":537000,"text":"And two months later when\nthe main plant opened"},{"time":541000,"text":"and hundreds of new\nworkers, white and black,"},{"time":543143,"text":"poured in to see the facility\nfor the first time,"},{"time":545501,"text":"they were met by the 16 foremen, white\nand black, standing shoulder to shoulder."},{"time":551000,"text":"They toured the facility and were asked\nif there were any questions, and"},{"time":555000,"text":"inevitably the same question arose:"},{"time":556000,"text":"\"Is this plant integrated or what?\""},{"time":558000,"text":"And one of the white foremen\nstepped forward and said,"},{"time":561000,"text":"\"You are being paid twice\nthe wages of any other workers"},{"time":565000,"text":"in this industry in this region\nand this is how we do business."},{"time":569000,"text":"Do you have any other questions?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"And there were none. In one fell swoop,"},{"time":575000,"text":"Mr. Teszler had integrated the textile\nindustry in that part of the South."},{"time":579000,"text":"It was an achievement\nworthy of Mahatma Gandhi,"},{"time":582000,"text":"conducted with the shrewdness of a lawyer\nand the idealism of a saint."},{"time":586000,"text":"In his eighties, Mr. Teszler, having\nretired from the textile industry,"},{"time":592000,"text":"adopted Wofford College,"},{"time":594000,"text":"auditing courses every semester,"},{"time":596000,"text":"and because he had a tendency\nto kiss anything that moved,"},{"time":600000,"text":"becoming affectionately known as \"Opi\"\n-- which is Magyar for grandfather --"},{"time":604000,"text":"by all and sundry. Before I got\nthere, the library of the college"},{"time":608000,"text":"had been named for Mr. Teszler,\nand after I arrived in 1993,"},{"time":613000,"text":"the faculty decided to honor itself by naming\nMr. Teszler Professor of the College --"},{"time":618000,"text":"partly because at that point\nhe had already taken"},{"time":621000,"text":"all of the courses in the catalog,\nbut mainly because"},{"time":624000,"text":"he was so conspicuously\nwiser than any one of us."},{"time":629000,"text":"To me, it was immensely reassuring\nthat the presiding spirit"},{"time":633000,"text":"of this little Methodist college\nin upstate South Carolina"},{"time":637000,"text":"was a Holocaust survivor\nfrom Central Europe."},{"time":641000,"text":"Wise he was, indeed, but he also\nhad a wonderful sense of humor."},{"time":645000,"text":"And once for an interdisciplinary class,"},{"time":648000,"text":"I was screening the opening segment\nof Ingmar Bergman's \"The Seventh Seal.\""},{"time":652000,"text":"As the medieval knight Antonius Block\nreturns from the wild goose chase"},{"time":656000,"text":"of the Crusades and arrives\non the rocky shore of Sweden,"},{"time":659000,"text":"only to find the specter\nof death waiting for him,"},{"time":662000,"text":"Mr. Teszler sat in the dark\nwith his fellow students. And"},{"time":666000,"text":"as death opened his cloak\nto embrace the knight"},{"time":670000,"text":"in a ghastly embrace, I heard\nMr. Teszler's tremulous voice:"},{"time":674000,"text":"\"Uh oh,\" he said, \"This doesn't\nlook so good.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":678000,"text":"But it was music that was his greatest\npassion, especially opera."},{"time":685000,"text":"And on the first occasion\nthat I visited his house, he gave me"},{"time":688000,"text":"honor of deciding what piece\nof music we would listen to."},{"time":692000,"text":"And I delighted him by rejecting\n\"Cavalleria Rusticana\""},{"time":696000,"text":"in favor of Bela\nBartok's \"Bluebeard's Castle.\""},{"time":699000,"text":"I love Bartok's music, as did Mr. Teszler,"},{"time":702000,"text":"and he had virtually every recording\nof Bartok's music ever issued."},{"time":706000,"text":"And it was at his house\nthat I heard for the first time"},{"time":708644,"text":"Bartok's Third Piano\nConcerto and learned from"},{"time":711000,"text":"Mr. Teszler that it had been composed\nin nearby Asheville, North Carolina"},{"time":716000,"text":"in the last year of the composer's life."},{"time":718000,"text":"He was dying of leukemia and he knew it,"},{"time":721000,"text":"and he dedicated this\nconcerto to his wife,"},{"time":724000,"text":"Dita, who was herself a concert pianist."},{"time":727000,"text":"And into the slow, second movement,\nmarked \"adagio religioso,\""},{"time":731000,"text":"he incorporated the sounds\nof birdsong that he heard"},{"time":735000,"text":"outside his window in what he knew\nwould be his last spring;"},{"time":738000,"text":"he was imagining a future for her\nin which he would play no part."},{"time":744000,"text":"And clearly this composition\nis his final statement to her --"},{"time":750000,"text":"it was first performed after his death --"},{"time":752000,"text":"and through her to the world."},{"time":754000,"text":"And just as clearly, it is saying,\n\"It's okay. It was all so beautiful."},{"time":761000,"text":"Whenever you hear this, I will be there.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":765000,"text":"It was only after Mr. Teszler's death\nthat I learned"},{"time":770000,"text":"that the marker on the grave of Bela\nBartok in Hartsdale, New York"},{"time":774000,"text":"was paid for by Sandor Teszler.\n\"Jó napot, Bela!\""},{"time":779000,"text":"Not long before Mr. Teszler’s\nown death at the age of 97,"},{"time":784000,"text":"he heard me hold forth on human iniquity."},{"time":788000,"text":"I delivered a lecture\nin which I described history"},{"time":790405,"text":"as, on the whole, a tidal wave\nof human suffering and brutality,"},{"time":794000,"text":"and Mr. Teszler came up to me afterwards\nwith gentle reproach and said,"},{"time":799000,"text":"\"You know, Doctor, human beings\nare fundamentally good.\""},{"time":805000,"text":"And I made a vow\nto myself, then and there,"},{"time":809000,"text":"that if this man who had such\ncause to think otherwise"},{"time":813000,"text":"had reached that conclusion,"},{"time":815000,"text":"I would not presume to differ\nuntil he released me from my vow."},{"time":819000,"text":"And now he's dead, so\nI'm stuck with my vow."},{"time":823000,"text":"\"Jó napot, Sandor!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"I thought my skein of Hungarian\nmentors had come to an end,"},{"time":829000,"text":"but almost immediately I met Francis\nRobicsek, a Hungarian doctor --"},{"time":836000,"text":"actually a heart surgeon in Charlotte, North\nCarolina, then in his late seventies --"},{"time":840000,"text":"who had been a pioneer\nin open-heart surgery,"},{"time":842167,"text":"and, tinkering away\nin his garage behind his house,"},{"time":846000,"text":"had invented many of the devices\nthat are standard parts of those procedures."},{"time":851000,"text":"He's also a prodigious art collector,\nbeginning as an intern in Budapest"},{"time":856000,"text":"by collecting 16th- and 17th-century\nDutch art and Hungarian painting,"},{"time":860000,"text":"and when he came to this country\nmoving on to Spanish colonial art,"},{"time":865000,"text":"Russian icons and finally Mayan ceramics."},{"time":868000,"text":"He's the author of seven books,\nsix of them on Mayan ceramics."},{"time":871000,"text":"It was he who broke the Mayan\ncodex, enabling scholars to relate"},{"time":875000,"text":"the pictographs on Mayan ceramics\nto the hieroglyphs of the Mayan script."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"On the occasion of my first\nvisit, we toured his house"},{"time":882000,"text":"and we saw hundreds\nof works of museum quality,"},{"time":885000,"text":"and then we paused in front of a closed\ndoor and Dr. Robicsek said,"},{"time":890000,"text":"with obvious pride, \"Now\nfor the piece De resistance.\""},{"time":893000,"text":"And he opened the door\nand we walked into a"},{"time":896000,"text":"windowless 20-by-20-foot room\nwith shelves from floor to ceiling, and"},{"time":902000,"text":"crammed on every shelf\nhis collection of Mayan ceramics."},{"time":904000,"text":"Now, I know absolutely nothing\nabout Mayan ceramics,"},{"time":906477,"text":"but I wanted to be as ingratiating\nas possible so I said,"},{"time":909477,"text":"\"But Dr. Robicsek, this\nis absolutely dazzling.\""},{"time":913000,"text":"\"Yes,\" he said. \"That\nis what the Louvre said."},{"time":916000,"text":"They would not leave me alone\nuntil I let them have a piece,"},{"time":920000,"text":"but it was not a good one.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"Well, it occurred to me\nthat I should invite Dr. Robicsek"},{"time":926000,"text":"to lecture at Wofford\nCollege on -- what else?"},{"time":929000,"text":"-- Leonardo da Vinci. And further,\nI should invite him to meet"},{"time":933000,"text":"my oldest trustee, who had majored\nin French history at Yale"},{"time":937000,"text":"some 70-odd years before and,\nat 89, still ruled the world's"},{"time":942000,"text":"largest privately owned textile\nempire with an iron hand."},{"time":947000,"text":"His name is Roger Milliken.\nAnd Mr. Milliken agreed,"},{"time":951000,"text":"and Dr. Robicsek agreed.\nAnd Dr. Robicsek visited"},{"time":954000,"text":"and delivered the lecture\nand it was a dazzling success."},{"time":957000,"text":"And afterwards we convened\nat the President's House with Dr. Robicsek"},{"time":961000,"text":"on one hand, Mr. Milliken on the other."},{"time":962000,"text":"And it was only at that moment,\nas we were sitting down to dinner,"},{"time":966000,"text":"that I recognized the enormity\nof the risk I had created,"},{"time":968739,"text":"because to bring these two titans,\nthese two masters of the universe"},{"time":972000,"text":"together -- it was like introducing Mothra\nto Godzilla over the skyline of Tokyo."},{"time":977000,"text":"If they didn't like each other,\nwe could all get trampled to death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980143,"text":"But they did, they did like each other."},{"time":982143,"text":"They got along famously\nuntil the very end of the meal,"},{"time":985000,"text":"and then they got into a furious argument."},{"time":987000,"text":"And what they were arguing about was this:"},{"time":989000,"text":"whether the second Harry Potter movie\nwas as good as the first. (Laughter)"},{"time":994000,"text":"Mr. Milliken said it was not.\nDr. Robicsek disagreed."},{"time":999000,"text":"I was still trying to take\nin the notion that these titans,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"these masters of the universe, in their spare\ntime watch Harry Potter movies,"},{"time":1006691,"text":"when Mr. Milliken thought\nhe would win the argument by saying,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"\"You just think it's so good\nbecause you didn't read the book.\""},{"time":1013000,"text":"And Dr. Robicsek reeled back in his chair,\nbut quickly gathered his wits,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"leaned forward and said, \"Well,\nthat is true, but I'll bet you went"},{"time":1020215,"text":"to the movie with a grandchild.\" \"Well,\nyes, I did,\" conceded Mr. Milliken."},{"time":1025000,"text":"\"Aha!\" said Dr. Robicsek. \"I went to the movie\nall by myself.\" (Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030000,"text":"And I realized, in this\nmoment of revelation,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"that what these two men were\nrevealing was the secret"},{"time":1039000,"text":"of their extraordinary success,\neach in his own right."},{"time":1042000,"text":"And it lay precisely\nin that insatiable curiosity,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"that irrepressible desire to know,\nno matter what the subject,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"no matter what the cost,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"even at a time when the keepers\nof the Doomsday Clock"},{"time":1055000,"text":"are willing to bet even money\nthat the human race won't be around"},{"time":1058120,"text":"to imagine anything in the year\n2100, a scant 93 years from now."},{"time":1063000,"text":"\"Live each day as if it\nis your last,\" said Mahatma Gandhi."},{"time":1067000,"text":"\"Learn as if you'll live forever.\""},{"time":1069000,"text":"This is what I'm passionate about.\nIt is precisely this."},{"time":1074000,"text":"It is this inextinguishable, undaunted\nappetite for learning and experience,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"no matter how risible,\nno matter how esoteric,"},{"time":1085215,"text":"no matter how seditious it might seem."},{"time":1088000,"text":"This defines the imagined futures\nof our fellow Hungarians --"},{"time":1094000,"text":"Robicsek, Teszler and Bartok\n-- as it does my own."},{"time":1099000,"text":"As it does, I suspect,\nthat of everybody here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1103000,"text":"To which I need only add, \"Ez\na mi munkank; es nem is keves.\""},{"time":1109000,"text":"This is our task; we know it will be hard."},{"time":1114000,"text":"\"Ez a mi munkank; es nem is keves.\nJó napot, pacák!\" (Applause)"}]}]}